# Phase 2 — Architecture Consolidation

**Goal:** No file over ~1,500 lines; no circular imports.

**Prerequisite:** Phase 0 gate green (`npm test`); Phase 1 hygiene landed (clean git, deploy strip wired).

**Exit criteria:** ESLint `import/no-cycle` passes on `public/src/**`; largest source file under 1,500 lines; `npm test` still green after each extraction chunk.

---

## Target layering (dependency direction)

```
utils, traits, schema, kernel/*     (leaf — no app imports)
        ↓
domain/*                            (game rules — no DOM, lit-html, valtio, services)
        ↓
state/*                             (persistence, reactive snapshots, managers)
        ↓
logic*.js / orchestration           (thin glue — shrink, then delete barrel)
        ↓
components/*, app.js                (DOM, lit-html, workers as consumers)
```

**Allowed sideways imports:** workers → `domain/heat`, `logic-heat-transfer`, `logic-topology` only (no DOM).

---

## Anti-patterns — do NOT do these

### Scope & sequencing

- **Do not split everything in one PR.** One module (or one cycle break) per commit; `npm test` after each.
- **Do not start with `Game` or `Engine`.** They sit at the center of the graph. Extract leaves first (`Part`, `Upgrade`, heat primitives already split).
- **Do not follow the Phase 2 table literally.** Several “logic.js” classes actually live in **`state.js`** today: `Reactor`, `GridManager`, `GameSaveManager`, `UnlockManager`, `LifecycleManager`, `ConfigManager`, `ExoticParticleManager`, `StateManager`. Plan extractions from the file that **currently owns** the code.
- **Do not mix Phase 3 UI polish** (responsive clipping, nav labels, screenshot diffs) or **Phase 1 deploy changes** into architecture commits.
- **Do not rename `@app/logic.js` public exports** until all tests and app imports are migrated — tests import `Game`, `BALANCE`, `getObjectiveCheck`, etc. from `@app/logic.js`.

### Circular imports

- **Do not “fix” `state ↔ logic` by adding a third file that imports both.** Introduce `domain/*` both can depend on; neither `state` nor `logic` should import each other when done.
- **Do not ignore `services ↔ state`.** `state.js` imports `queryClient` / `leaderboardService` from `services.js`; `services.js` imports schemas and save helpers from `state.js`. Break this cycle in Phase 2, not only `state ↔ logic`.
- **Do not leave `logic-upgrade-dom.js → state.js`** while claiming cycles are fixed. DOM binding must not pull reactive state; pass affordances in or move getters to domain.
- **Do not enable `import/no-cycle: error` globally on day one.** Add the rule, run on `public/src`, fix cycles incrementally; use `warn` until the graph is clean, then tighten to `error`.
- **Do not use dynamic `import()` purely to silence cycle lint** without restructuring — that hides the problem and breaks static analysis.

### Domain purity (`domain/*`)

- **Do not put lit-html, `document.*`, or `window.*` in `domain/*`.** `Part.createElement()`, `ObjectiveController` toast DOM, and `Game` visibility listeners in `logic.js` are presentation/orchestration — keep in `components/*` or a `presentation/*` layer, not domain.
- **Do not move `Part` / `PartSet` wholesale to `domain/part.js`** without splitting data (`recalculate_stats`, catalogs) from DOM (`createElement`, `setAffordable` + `getPartElement`). Current `Part` calls `renderToNode`, `bindPartElement`, `document.querySelectorAll`.
- **Do not import `components/button-factory.js`, `ui-components.js`, or `services.js` from domain.** `logic.js` already violates this (lines ~211–214); new modules must not copy the pattern.
- **Do not import Valtio (`proxy`, `subscribe`) in domain.** Reactive state belongs in `state/*`.
- **Do not pull workers into domain modules** — keep worker-safe heat/topology in existing `logic-heat-transfer.js` / `logic-topology.js` or thin `domain/heat` re-exports; workers must not load lit-html or state.

### State split (`state.js` → `state/*`)

- **Do not create `state/logic.js` or re-export from `logic.js` inside state.** State depends on domain physics helpers currently imported from `logic.js` (`deriveReactorStats`, `applyCellMultipliers`, etc.) — move those to `domain/reactor-stats.js` or `kernel/physics.js` first, then point state at domain.
- **Do not split save Zod schemas away from `parseAndValidateSave` call sites** without keeping a single public entry (`state/save.js` exports everything save-related).
- **Do not break `store.js` consumers.** `store.js` is the public facade re-exporting `state.js`; keep it stable or update `app.js` / components in the same chunk.
- **Do not duplicate preferences in both `state/preferences.js` and `logic.js`.**

### Logic barrel (`logic.js`)

- **Do not delete `logic.js` until the barrel re-exports zero remaining implementations.** During migration, `logic.js` should re-export from new modules so `@app/logic.js` tests keep working.
- **Do not leave `logic.js` as a 7k-line re-export file.** End state: thin barrel (<200 lines) or redirect to `domain/*` + delete.
- **Do not move `Game` (line ~7147) before its state managers exist in domain/state.** `Game` imports `GridManager`, `GameSaveManager`, `Reactor`, etc. from `state.js` — extract managers first or co-locate in `domain/game.js` with explicit dependency order.

### UI split (`components/ui.js` ~3,400 lines)

- **Do not create circular UI modules** (`ui.js` ↔ `ui-reactor.js`). Feature modules import shared layout helpers; `ui.js` becomes a thin composer.
- **Do not duplicate what already exists:** `ui-modals.js`, `ui-components.js`, `ui-grid.js`, `page-setup-ui.js`, `ui-tooltips-tutorial.js` — extend these instead of parallel `ui-*` trees.
- **Do not import `logic.js` for one class** when a narrower import works (`ObjectiveController` → future `domain/objectives.js` or `components/objectives.js` depending on DOM).

### Workers & performance

- **Do not change worker import paths without running** `tests/core/workers/**` and `tests/core/thermodynamics/**`.
- **Do not bundle `domain/*` through `logic.js` in workers** — workers already import `logic-heat-transfer.js` and `logic-topology.js` directly; preserve that.

### Tests & tooling

- **Do not update every test import to `@app/domain/part.js` in one commit.** Migrate implementation first; keep `@app/logic.js` barrel; switch tests last optional pass.
- **Do not delete tests that fail during extraction** — fix imports or restore barrel exports.
- **Do not skip `npm test` for “mechanical move only”** — line moves can break Vitest alias resolution and side-effect order.

### Line-count gaming

- **Do not split at exactly 1,500 lines** with arbitrary cuts — split by cohesion (one class family, one concern).
- **Do not count re-export barrels toward the 1,500 limit** while implementation remains in a god file behind them.
- **Do not ignore `objectives.css` (2,455 lines)** in Phase 2 — CSS split is Phase 3 unless a file blocks tests; focus Phase 2 on JS architecture.

