## Correct extraction order (recommended)

| Order | Module | From | Notes |
|-------|--------|------|-------|
| 1 | `domain/reactor-stats.js` | `logic.js` exports used by `state.js` | Breaks state→logic edge first |
| 2 | `domain/part.js` | `Part`, `PartSet` | Split DOM methods to `logic-upgrade-dom` / button-factory |
| 3 | `domain/upgrade.js` | `Upgrade`, `UpgradeSet` | Same DOM split as parts |
| 4 | `domain/grid.js` | `Tile`, `Tileset` + `GridManager` from **state.js** | GridManager currently in state |
| 5 | `domain/heat.js` | `HeatSystem`, `HeatFlowVisualizer` | Align with existing heat-transfer split |
| 6 | `domain/engine.js` | `Engine`, `Performance` | After heat + grid stable |
| 7 | `domain/objectives.js` | `ObjectiveManager` (data) | Keep `ObjectiveController` DOM in components |
| 8 | `domain/game.js` | `Game` + managers from **state.js** | Largest move — last |
| 9 | `state/preferences.js`, `state/save.js`, `state/ui-state.js` | `state.js` | After domain decoupled |
| 10 | `components/ui-*.js` feature splits | `ui.js` | Reactor page, upgrades page, shell wiring |

Each row = one or more commits + `npm test`.

---

## Correct patterns — do this instead

| Step | Action |
|------|--------|
| 1 | Add ESLint `import/no-cycle` (warn) to `config/eslint.config.js` for `public/src/**/*.js` |
| 2 | Inventory cycles with `npx eslint public/src --rule 'import/no-cycle: error'` or dependency-cruiser |
| 3 | Move shared physics/stats from `logic.js` → `domain/` so `state.js` stops importing `logic.js` |
| 4 | Extract one class family; leave re-exports in `logic.js` / `state.js` |
| 5 | Run `npm test`; fix only regressions caused by the extraction |
| 6 | Repeat until largest file < 1,500 lines and cycles = 0 |
| 7 | Tighten `import/no-cycle` to `error` |

---

## Verification checklist

```bash
npx eslint public/src -c config/eslint.config.js --rule "import/no-cycle: error"
npm test
```

Optional line audit (PowerShell):

```powershell
Get-ChildItem public/src -Recurse -Filter *.js |
  ForEach-Object { [PSCustomObject]@{ Lines = (Get-Content $_.FullName | Measure-Object -Line).Lines; Name = $_.FullName } } |
  Sort-Object Lines -Descending | Select-Object -First 15
```

All files under `public/src` should be < 1,500 lines (except generated/vendor). `npm test` must pass.

