## Known repo landmines

| Issue | Location | Risk |
|-------|----------|------|
| **state → logic** | `state.js` imports `deriveReactorStats`, `applyCellMultipliers`, … | Blocker for cycle-free graph |
| **logic → state** | `logic.js` imports `GridManager`, `Reactor`, `GameSaveManager`, … | Mutual dependency |
| **services ↔ state** | `services.js` ↔ `state.js` | Second cycle often missed |
| **logic → components** | `logic.js` imports button-factory, ui-components | Domain contamination |
| **Part DOM in model** | `Part.createElement()` in `logic.js` ~967 | Cannot naively move to domain |
| **ObjectiveController DOM** | `logic.js` ~2507+ | Belongs in components after split |
| **Managers in state, Game in logic** | `state.js` classes vs `Game` in `logic.js` | Plan table ≠ current layout |
| **Workers** | `gameLoopWorkerCore.js`, `physicsWorkerCore.js` | Must keep importing heat/topology without DOM |
| **Test barrel** | `@app/logic.js` in 10+ tests | Keep re-exports until end |
| **store.js facade** | Re-exports all of `state.js` | Update atomically with state split |
| **Existing partial splits** | `logic-heat-transfer`, `logic-topology`, `logic-upgrade-dom`, `kernel/physics` | Extend, don’t duplicate |

